# VetTrack — Cursor rules (architecture invariants)

These rules govern **all AI-assisted development** on this repository: a production veterinary hospital operations stack (React/Vite + Express + PostgreSQL + Drizzle + BullMQ/Redis + Clerk + Dexie offline sync). They supplement stacked project rules under `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` (especially `engineering-and-agent-principles.mdc`, `typescript-standards.mdc`, `express-server.mdc`). Prefer **evidence from `server/`, `src/`, `shared/`** over generic advice.

**How to use:** Keep this file at the repo root; work **one focused feature at a time**; after substantive edits run `npx tsc --noEmit` (zero errors before merge). Schema-first: start with `server/db.ts` before routes/UI.

---

## Multi-tenancy

- Treat **`clinicId` as a security boundary**, not a stylistic filter: every `select` / `insert` / `update` / `delete` against tenant data must constrain rows by the **request’s** `clinicId` (from `req.authUser.clinicId` / `req.clinicId` after auth middleware — see `server/middleware/auth.ts`).
- **Never infer tenant scope only from a join** on another table; the **target row’s table** must include `eq(table.clinicId, clinicId)` (or equivalent) so OR conditions cannot widen tenancy.
- The string **`dev-clinic-default`** is the dev-bypass default clinic (`server/middleware/auth.ts` `DEV_USER`); **never hardcode** it in production-only code paths. Production **must** have `CLERK_SECRET_KEY` or the server refuses to start (`server/middleware/auth.ts`).
- Cross-clinic reads/writes are **security defects**, not style issues.
- New `pgTable` definitions in **`server/db.ts`** must include **`clinicId`** scoped to the clinic/tenant (pattern used across `vt_*` tables). Follow existing table ordering in that file for consistency.

## Auth

- **Auth mode (contract):** `server/lib/auth-mode.ts` — `clerk` when `CLERK_SECRET_KEY` is set **and** `CLERK_ENABLED !== "false"`; otherwise `dev-bypass`. **`resolveAuthModeFromEnv()`** is used for startup logging and tooling.
- **Runtime API auth (`resolveAuthUser`):** Development bypass applies when **`NODE_ENV !== "production"`** and **`CLERK_SECRET_KEY` is absent** (`server/middleware/auth.ts`). Clerk middleware is mounted only when `authModeResolution.mode === "clerk"` (`server/index.ts`).
- **`sessionContextMiddleware`** (`server/middleware/auth.ts`) runs globally on `/api` and **best-effort** attaches `req.authUser`, `req.clinicId`, `req.locale` without returning 401; routes that require authentication must still use **`requireAuth`** / **`requireAuthAny`**.
- **Role source of truth:** After Clerk upsert, **`role` is always read from `vt_users.role`** in the database; JWT/session claims are **not** trusted for authorization (`server/middleware/auth.ts` comment near upsert).
- **Numeric role floor** (`ROLE_HIERARCHY` in `server/middleware/auth.ts`): `admin` **40**, `vet` **30**, `senior_technician` **25**, `lead_technician` **22**, `technician` / `vet_tech` **20**, `student` **10**. **`requireRole(minRole)`** compares these floors.
- **Middleware:** `requireAuth` — active users only (`status === "pending"` → 403 `ACCOUNT_PENDING_APPROVAL`; `status === "blocked"` → 403 `ACCOUNT_BLOCKED`); `requireAdmin` — **`role === "admin"`** only; `requireRole(minRole)` — DB role hierarchy; **`requireEffectiveRole(minRole)`** — uses **`resolveCurrentRole`** (`server/lib/role-resolution.js`) for shift-context effective role; admins short-circuit.
- **Deleted users:** `deletedAt` set → 403 with **`ACCOUNT_DELETED`** (`server/middleware/auth.ts`).
- **Dev-only headers** (`X-Dev-Role-Override`, `X-Dev-User-ID-Override`, `X-Dev-Clinic-ID-Override`): honored only in **development bypass** path (`server/middleware/auth.ts`).

## Database schema

- **Single source of truth:** all Drizzle table definitions live in **`server/db.ts`** only.
- **Authoring workflow:** edit **`server/db.ts`** → **`npx drizzle-kit generate`** → **`pnpm db:migrate`**. Use **`npx drizzle-kit push`** only for **local dev** — never against production (`CLAUDE.md`).
- **Boot behavior:** **`server/index.ts`** calls **`runMigrations()`** from **`server/migrate.ts`** before starting background schedulers; pending SQL migrations apply at process start.
- Table names use the **`vt_`** prefix (e.g. `vt_users`, `vt_billing_ledger`).
- **Soft delete:** pattern `deletedAt` / `deletedBy` where present — queries must filter **`isNull(table.deletedAt)`** unless intentionally including deleted rows (users, equipment, folders, formulary, etc.).
- **`vt_equipment`:** optimistic locking via **`version`** — updates must increment **`version`** and enforce expected version on write where the codebase already does (follow existing equipment routes/services).
- **Formulary uniqueness:** filtered unique on **`(clinicId, genericName, concentrationMgMl)`** with **`WHERE deleted_at IS NULL`** (see `server/db.ts` `drugFormulary` indexes).
- **JSONB** (`metadata`, `calculationSnapshot`, payloads): pass **typed objects** through Drizzle; never build SQL by concatenating JSON strings.

## Service layer

- **`server/services/`** exports **async functions** (no service classes); **`clinicId` is an explicit parameter** — never read from global/env for tenant scope.
- Return **typed DTOs** or throw **domain errors** (e.g. **`MedTaskError`**, **`MedicationCalculationError`**, **`InventoryError`** patterns).
- Multi-step writes: **`await db.transaction(async (tx) => { ... })`** for atomicity.
- **`logAudit()`** (`server/lib/audit.ts`): **do not `await`** on critical paths unless passing **`tx`** for same-transaction audit; non-tx call wraps its own transaction and **swallows errors** — treat as fire-and-forget from handlers.
- **`insertRealtimeDomainEvent(tx, { clinicId, type, payload })`** (`server/lib/realtime-outbox.ts`): call **inside the same transaction** as the domain write so outbox rows roll back with failed commits.

## Transactional event outbox

- Domain-facing realtime: insert into **`vt_event_outbox`** via **`insertRealtimeDomainEvent`** in the **same DB transaction** as the mutation (`server/lib/realtime-outbox.ts`).
- **Publisher:** **`server/lib/event-publisher.ts`** polls every **`750`** ms (`POLL_MS`), batch size **100**, backoff constants **`OUTBOX_MAX_RETRY_COUNT = 50`** for DLQ — do not build parallel polling loops for the same table.
- **`outboxEmitter`** (`server/lib/event-publisher.ts`) emits after publish; consumers attach there for push/SSE fan-out — follow existing patterns instead of ad-hoc DB polling for “live” UX.
- **`logAudit`** without `tx` also inserts **`vt_event_outbox`** rows with type **`audit_log`** (`OUTBOX_TYPE_AUDIT_LOG`).

## Background workers (BullMQ / schedulers)

- Register every new worker/scheduler startup path in **`server/app/start-schedulers.ts`** (e.g. **`await startExpiryCheckWorker()`**, **`await startChargeAlertWorker()`**, **`await startInventoryDeductionWorker()`**, **`await startIntegrationWorker()`**, plus **`startErIntakeEscalationScheduler`**, **`startErHandoffSlaScheduler`**, etc.). If it is not started here, it does not run in production.
- **Redis:** optional in dev — workers log disabled when Redis is missing; production expects Redis for queues (`server/workers/chargeAlertWorker.ts`, `inventory-deduction.worker.ts` patterns).
- **Charge alert queue:** `charge-alert`, job name **`check-plug`**, deterministic **`jobId`** via **`buildChargeAlertJobId(returnId)`** (`plug-check-${returnId}`); enqueue with **`delay`** from deadline minutes; cancel with **`cancelChargeAlertJob`** / **`job.remove()`** when plug-in state clears (`server/workers/chargeAlertWorker.ts`).
- **Cron-style queues:** e.g. expiry worker uses BullMQ **repeat** / cron patterns — do not replace with **`setInterval`** for those domains (see `server/workers/expiryCheckWorker.ts`).
- **Inventory deduction:** medication task completion enqueues **`vt_inventory_jobs`** and BullMQ processes **`inventory-deduction`** queue (`server/workers/inventory-deduction.worker.ts`); **`recoverPendingInventoryJobs`** runs on startup and on a **`10 * 60 * 1000`** ms interval (`server/index.ts`, `server/lib/inventory-job-recovery.ts`) — keep this recovery path.
- **ER schedulers (not BullMQ):** intake escalation **`startErIntakeEscalationScheduler`** — **`setInterval(..., 60 * 1000)`** (`server/services/er-intake-escalation.service.ts`); handoff SLA **`startErHandoffSlaScheduler`** — **`setInterval(..., 5 * 60 * 1000)`** (`server/services/er-handoff-sla.service.ts`).

## Medication safety

- **Liquid draw volume:** **`volumeMl = (weightKg * prescribedDoseMgPerKg) / concentrationMgPerMl`** with **`prescribedDoseMgPerKg`** derived from prescribed dose + unit (`server/services/medication-calculation.service.ts` **`calculateMedicationVolumeMl`**). Tablet flows use tablet math — see same file when `doseUnit === "tablet"`.
- **Hard upper bound:** calculated volume must satisfy **`volumeMl > 0`** and **`volumeMl < 100`** ml (**`MAX_SAFE_VOLUME_ML`** / **`MAX_EXCLUSIVE_VOLUME_ML`**); validation errors use **`MedicationCalculationError`** / **`MedTaskError`** with statuses defined on those classes (routes map them — see `server/routes/medication-tasks.ts`).
- **Safety levels** from dose deviation: **`blocked`** / **`critical`** / **`warning`** / **`safe`** (`medication-calculation.service.ts`). **`blocked`** doses **cannot be created** as tasks (`createMedicationTask` throws **`DOSE_BLOCKED`**).
- **Warnings:** when **`requiresReason`** is true, **`overrideReason`** must be provided on create (`REASON_REQUIRED`).
- **Snapshot shape** stored on **`vt_medication_tasks.calculationSnapshot`:** **`{ version: 1, data: CalculationResult }`** (`server/services/medication-tasks.service.ts`).
- **Completion:** **`validateCompletionVolume`** enforces finite volume, **`> 0`**, **`< 100`**, and **at most two decimal places** (`server/services/medication-tasks.service.ts`).
- **Duplicate open tasks:** one row per **`(clinicId, animalId, drugId, route)`** with **`status IN ('pending','in_progress')`** — enforced by DB partial unique index + **`findOpenMedicationTaskDuplicate`** (`server/services/medication-tasks.service.ts`).
- **Valid routes:** **`IV`**, **`IM`**, **`PO`**, **`SC`** (normalized uppercase).

## Billing & idempotency

- **`vt_billing_ledger`:** **`idempotency_key`** is **`notNull().unique()`** — duplicates must be handled by **idempotent read-or-insert** / **`ON CONFLICT`** patterns (`server/lib/equipment-seen.ts`, `server/services/appointments.service.ts` patterns).
- **`animalId`** is **nullable** on **`vt_billing_ledger`** for pre-patient captures (`server/db.ts` comment).
- **Status enum:** **`pending` → `synced` → `voided`** (`billingLedgerStatusEnum` in `server/db.ts`); design transitions explicitly — no silent backwards moves.
- **`vt_usage_sessions`:** billing lifecycle uses **`startedAt`**, **`lastBilledThrough`**, **`endedAt`**, **`status`** — follow existing session billing services when closing sessions.

## ER (emergency)

- **Escalation timing:** per-clinic columns **`erIntakeEscalateLowMinutes`** and **`erIntakeEscalateMediumMinutes`** on **`vt_clinics`** (defaults **15** / **15** in `server/db.ts`). **`computeInitialEscalatesAt`** (`server/services/er-intake-escalation.service.ts`): **`low`** → now + low minutes; **`medium`** → now + medium minutes; **`high`** → **`escalatesAt = null`** (no auto timer). Scheduler runs **`scanErIntakeEscalations`** on a **`60`** second tick (same file).
- **Handoff SLA:** constant **`ER_HANDOFF_SLA_MINUTES = 60`** (`server/services/er-board.service.ts`); breach scan sets **`slaBreachedAt`** and emits **`ER_HANDOFF_SLA_BREACHED`** via outbox (`server/services/er-handoff-sla.service.ts`). Scheduler interval **`5`** minutes.
- **Routes:** **`server/routes/er.ts`** uses **`requireAuth`** globally; **`requireAssignableRole`** allows **`admin` | `vet` | `senior_technician` | `technician`** for assign/handoff POST/PATCH; **`PATCH /mode`** uses **`requireRole("admin")`**.
- **`vt_er_board_event_log`:** **append-only** event history (`server/db.ts`) — do not **`UPDATE`** / **`DELETE`** rows; insert new events only.

## Offline-first & sync

- All browser API traffic goes through **`src/lib/api.ts`** **`request()`** / helpers — do not scatter raw **`fetch()`** for backend calls in feature code.
- When **`request()`** receives **`offline`** options and the failure is a **network** error, the call **must** enqueue **`pendingSync`** in Dexie (**`addPendingSync`** / **`offline-db.ts`**) — never drop the mutation silently.
- **`src/lib/sync-engine.ts`:** **`MAX_RETRIES = 5`**; delay bases **`RETRY_DELAYS_MS = [2000, 5000, 10000]`** (additional retries reuse the last delay); **`CIRCUIT_THRESHOLD = 5`** consecutive transient failures opens circuit **`20000`** ms; items use **`ITEM_TIMEOUT_MS = 30000`** for fetch attempts.
- Dexie: **`offline-db.ts`** — bump **`this.version(n)`** when adding stores/indexes; never edit a lower version in place.

## API client & types

- New endpoints: add a typed **`request<T>()`** wrapper in **`src/lib/api.ts`** and types under **`src/types/`** (import pattern at top of `api.ts`).
- Use **`request<MyType>(...)`** generics for JSON responses.
- **Timeouts:** default **`FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS = 30_000`**; equipment list **`EQUIPMENT_LIST_FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS = 5_000`**; task dashboards **`TASKS_FETCH_TIMEOUT_MS = 5_000`** (`src/lib/api.ts`) — pass **`timeoutMs`** for operational screens.
- **401:** GET-like handling triggers soft navigation to **`/signin`** guarded by **`authRedirectInProgress`** to avoid redirect storms (`src/lib/api.ts`).

## Frontend routing

- Route-level pages live under **`src/pages/`** and are **`lazy(() => import(...))`**-loaded from **`src/app/routes.tsx`**.
- **Chunk load failures:** global handling lives in **`main.tsx`** — do not duplicate chunk error handlers in individual pages.

## Technology constraints

- **UI:** **Shadcn** patterns / existing primitives — do not add alternate component frameworks (MUI/Chakra/Ant) unless explicitly directed.
- **Icons:** **Lucide React** only.
- **Animation:** **Framer Motion** for motion primitives in this codebase.
- **ORM:** **Drizzle** query builder — avoid new raw **`db.execute`** strings for app logic.
- **HTTP:** **Express** only for the API server.
- **Jobs:** **BullMQ** (+ Redis) for queue workers; use **`setInterval`** only for **small in-process schedulers** already used (ER scans, inventory job recovery) — not as a substitute for BullMQ domain queues.
- **Offline DB:** **Dexie** (see **`src/lib/offline-db.ts`**).
- **Auth provider:** **Clerk** — no custom JWT minting for production auth.

## Internationalization

- Hebrew copy only in **`locales/he.json`**, **`locales/en.json`**, and UI strings — **not** in identifiers, filenames, logs, or DB/API field names.
- Frontend **`import { t } from '@/lib/i18n'`**; backend uses **`i18nMiddleware`** / **`req.locale`** (`server/index.ts`, `lib/i18n/middleware.js`) for localized **responses** — avoid hardcoding Hebrew in route strings.

## Security

- **XSS:** global JSON body sanitization with **`xss`** runs before handlers (`server/index.ts` after **`express.json()`**).
- **Rate limits** (`server/middleware/rate-limiters.ts`): global **`120`** req/min per IP on `/api`; **`scanLimiter`** **`10`**/min; **`checkoutLimiter`** **`20`**/min; add scoped limiters for new sensitive write endpoints.
- **Integration secrets:** encrypt at rest when **`DB_CONFIG_ENCRYPTION_KEY`** is set; never log secrets.
- **Integration webhooks:** verify **HMAC** on raw body routes (`server/index.ts` mounts **`/api/integration-webhooks/:adapterId`** before JSON parser).
- **CSP / Helmet:** extending **`connectSrc`**, **`scriptSrc`**, etc. requires updating **`server/index.ts`** Helmet `contentSecurityPolicy.directives`.

## Development workflow

1. Schema / enum change → **`server/db.ts`**
2. **`npx drizzle-kit generate`** → SQL under **`migrations/`**
3. **`pnpm db:migrate`**
4. New Express router → **`server/routes/*.ts`** → register in **`server/app/routes.ts`**
5. New BullMQ worker → wire **`startXxxWorker`** in **`server/app/start-schedulers.ts`**
6. Client **`src/lib/api.ts`** + **`src/types/`**
7. New page → **`src/pages/`** + **`src/app/routes.tsx`** `lazy` route
8. **`npx tsc --noEmit`** — must pass with **zero** errors before commit/PR

